div.p:
Now the whole World saw that they least intended what they most pretended;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
Homer they that sit at our helme looked one way but rowed another, whey they should make his Majesty glorious, they summon all the wit and malice of their side to make him infamous; when they should bring him to his Throne they bring him to the Scaffold, the Liberty they with much blood and treasure obtained for the Parliament is it seemes an unparalleld force; the Religion to be established are all the antiquated and condemned errours and heresies with the exploded Schismes that attended them, so many Religions that sober & unconcerned Spectators thought we had none, so easy is it in a throng of Religions to loose Religion.
